place.name: TATTERSETT
place.gazetteerText: TATTERSETT, or Gatesend, a parish in Walsingham district, Norfolk; 4¾ miles W of Fakenham r. station. Post town, Raynham, under Br and on. Acres, 1,759. Real property, £2,697. Pop., 205. Houses, 33. The manor belongs to J. S. Chad, Esq. The living is a rectory, annexed to Tatterford. The church is later English. Charities, £5. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
